# Cursor — repo rules

See `AGENTS.md` in the repo root. That is the canonical context file
for this repository — read it first before making any changes.

If you only have time for one section, read **§0 TL;DR** (top of file)
— it lists the 5 rules whose violation has cost real money or required
emergency patches in production.

This file exists so Cursor auto-loads project context. It deliberately
contains no rules of its own — keeping a single source of truth in
`AGENTS.md` prevents drift between the two files.
